posts.description: Just me in vintage jeans and a lack of showers for three days kinda feeling. Travel is oh so glamours! (in theory)
If I could I would make this light all day everyday and I would never ever be sick of it! Doesn't matter where I am - when I see this light I find my heart fills with love for the world!

Parenting tip 1. When road tripping with teen don't gift your child all three Hunger Games books. If you do, every stop and beautiful scene you want to go see will be met with utter disdain because that teens brain will be full of stories swirling and pulling her out to see another beach will be met with scenes like this!

Teens. Nearly adult! Youths. Young people. I wish I knew how to be a parent better then I do but I guess we all do our best and then we all learn to work through whatever we are given. Maybe that's the plan? Maybe not knowing what to do sometimes is good for us!
Cow kisses are special and very rare. This is Buster he is lovely!
On the tips of your fingers

Thinking about being an artist and the jump between creating content I'm wanting to create and the living I need to make. There seems to be so much in my brain to make and I'm not sure how to get it all out!! Her hair reminds me of a giant paint brush. Giant leaps I've made in things I want to do and still so many leaps to go. Remembering to be grateful along the way helps me....stops me from chasing goals all the time and instead enjoy the journey. Can u believe I'm freaking still talking about gratefulness! ðŸ™„#becauseineedit

Things in nature endlessly amuse me and the road trip would be enough for me if all we did was collect and take photos and scour and search for funny treasures. Here are two sea sponge hands, I wanted to keep these funny sponge hands. Then after being told by both daughters they will stink and we shouldn't take things and what are you even going to do with them? I left them sitting on a rock for someone else to enjoy! #parentbeingparented

This is how my heart feels when all of us are together in the late afternoon sun. The days are setting on us being just us... the girls own lives develop more and more and it is all about letting go and taking a more minor role in the movie of their lives. We captured them both and drove off on this road trip. It is both fun and squishy and a long long drive... What a gift it all is.

Little things aren't little. Small bright red flower shaped like a little cage. I love! My favourite thing is to have time. Time is a delightful thing... time to wander and play and spontaneously follow a path or pick strange flowers and remark at the little delights of life.
